      "side": 1,
      "message": "GenerateConfig{} leaves AllSchemas false, so generation only emits components.schemas entries that are referenced from a schema position in the document. The openapiv2.txtar test shows the consequence: extracting openapi.json yields #Foo, but `cue export --out openapi` of that CUE drops Foo entirely (expect-generate has no components), because paths is empty and nothing references it.\n\nFor a `cue import openapi:` -\u003e `cue export --out openapi` round trip that\u0027s a silent fidelity loss of component schemas. Given the commit message frames this as round-tripping a complete document, is dropping unreferenced schemas intended here? Setting AllSchemas: true would preserve every top-level definition as a components.schemas entry, which seems closer to a faithful round trip. If the current behavior is deliberate, a one-line comment noting why would help.",
      "revId": "8541f8de85a4a7ec6efdf3de7b0b642e8da13b0c",
